00:02:28.446 --> 00:02:29.916 A:middle
&gt;&gt; So, this film, along with the

00:02:29.916 --> 00:02:31.926 A:middle
others beautifully depicts the

00:02:31.926 --> 00:02:33.876 A:middle
impact accessible tech has on

00:02:33.876 --> 00:02:35.856 A:middle
people's lives when you design

00:02:35.856 --> 00:02:37.886 A:middle
for everyone, including people

00:02:37.886 --> 00:02:39.266 A:middle
with a range of disabilities.

00:02:39.996 --> 00:02:41.956 A:middle
I'm here today to ask you to

00:02:41.956 --> 00:02:43.856 A:middle
join the campaign with us in

00:02:43.856 --> 00:02:45.936 A:middle
designing your apps and games to

00:02:45.936 --> 00:02:47.176 A:middle
work for everyone too.

00:02:47.976 --> 00:02:50.326 A:middle
Because we inherently design for

00:02:50.326 --> 00:02:52.166 A:middle
ourselves, because we design to

00:02:52.166 --> 00:02:54.076 A:middle
what we know, our own world

00:02:54.076 --> 00:02:54.556 A:middle
view.

00:02:55.196 --> 00:02:56.616 A:middle
We have wants and needs, and

00:02:56.616 --> 00:02:57.266 A:middle
passions.

00:02:57.646 --> 00:02:59.086 A:middle
We think of features, make an

00:02:59.556 --> 00:03:01.236 A:middle
app, join a company to put those

00:03:01.236 --> 00:03:03.036 A:middle
ideas out there for others too.

00:03:04.006 --> 00:03:06.516 A:middle
But regardless, the next step of

00:03:06.516 --> 00:03:08.386 A:middle
reaching more people is putting

00:03:08.386 --> 00:03:10.036 A:middle
yourself in their shoes.

00:03:10.626 --> 00:03:12.816 A:middle
We need to figure out who we

00:03:12.816 --> 00:03:13.956 A:middle
might be excluding.

00:03:14.776 --> 00:03:15.886 A:middle
Have you thought about how there

00:03:15.886 --> 00:03:17.286 A:middle
might be other people out in the

00:03:17.286 --> 00:03:18.666 A:middle
world with the same passions,

00:03:18.666 --> 00:03:20.276 A:middle
needs and wants as you, but

00:03:20.276 --> 00:03:22.426 A:middle
can't use your app?

00:03:22.956 --> 00:03:25.176 A:middle
If we think about how there are

00:03:25.176 --> 00:03:27.536 A:middle
more than one billion active

00:03:27.536 --> 00:03:29.306 A:middle
Apple devices out there, which

00:03:29.306 --> 00:03:31.096 A:middle
is a lot of potential customers,

00:03:31.586 --> 00:03:33.506 A:middle
and knowing that one in seven

00:03:33.676 --> 00:03:34.656 A:middle
people in the world have a

00:03:34.656 --> 00:03:37.336 A:middle
disability, we can be sure that

00:03:37.336 --> 00:03:38.676 A:middle
people who may want to use our

00:03:38.676 --> 00:03:40.816 A:middle
apps and platforms will lie

00:03:40.816 --> 00:03:42.716 A:middle
everywhere across a spectrum of

00:03:42.716 --> 00:03:44.116 A:middle
abilities and capabilities.

00:03:46.366 --> 00:03:48.586 A:middle
Human abilities vary greatly

00:03:48.586 --> 00:03:50.176 A:middle
across cognition and social

00:03:50.176 --> 00:03:52.546 A:middle
abilities; dexterity, mobility,

00:03:52.786 --> 00:03:53.956 A:middle
vision and hearing.

00:03:54.376 --> 00:03:56.476 A:middle
And in order to understand and

00:03:56.476 --> 00:03:58.166 A:middle
comprehend information, our

00:03:58.166 --> 00:04:00.586 A:middle
perception through sight, sound

00:04:00.586 --> 00:04:02.396 A:middle
and touch are essential.

00:04:03.496 --> 00:04:05.066 A:middle
What happens if you inhibit one

00:04:05.066 --> 00:04:06.826 A:middle
of those senses, or take one

00:04:06.826 --> 00:04:07.256 A:middle
away?

00:04:07.696 --> 00:04:09.906 A:middle
That could happen to you or I in

00:04:09.906 --> 00:04:11.506 A:middle
our lifetime, gradually or

00:04:11.506 --> 00:04:12.396 A:middle
instantaneously.

00:04:12.976 --> 00:04:15.206 A:middle
People with physical

00:04:15.206 --> 00:04:16.496 A:middle
disabilities will include

00:04:16.496 --> 00:04:18.016 A:middle
extreme cases, like cerebral

00:04:18.016 --> 00:04:20.436 A:middle
palsy and paralysis, but also

00:04:20.436 --> 00:04:22.206 A:middle
include conditions like carpal

00:04:22.206 --> 00:04:24.236 A:middle
tunnel syndrome, or temporary

00:04:24.236 --> 00:04:25.306 A:middle
conditions such as a broken

00:04:25.306 --> 00:04:25.660 A:middle
wrist.

00:04:27.776 --> 00:04:29.816 A:middle
People with vision loss will

00:04:29.816 --> 00:04:31.946 A:middle
include blindness, low vision,

00:04:31.946 --> 00:04:33.076 A:middle
and colorblindness.

00:04:33.646 --> 00:04:34.776 A:middle
But also, situational

00:04:34.776 --> 00:04:36.486 A:middle
disabilities like screen glare

00:04:36.866 --> 00:04:38.516 A:middle
and temporary day blindness that

00:04:38.516 --> 00:04:40.036 A:middle
we all experience when emerging

00:04:40.036 --> 00:04:43.556 A:middle
from a dark movie theater.

00:04:43.696 --> 00:04:45.026 A:middle
Hearing loss is one of the

00:04:45.026 --> 00:04:46.176 A:middle
leading types of hearing

00:04:46.176 --> 00:04:46.966 A:middle
disabilities.

00:04:47.396 --> 00:04:48.776 A:middle
Whether it's from birth or it's

00:04:48.776 --> 00:04:50.506 A:middle
prevalent with age, made for

00:04:50.556 --> 00:04:52.276 A:middle
iPhone hearing aids are changing

00:04:52.426 --> 00:04:53.896 A:middle
people's quality of life.

00:04:54.336 --> 00:04:56.046 A:middle
And as we extend our

00:04:56.046 --> 00:04:57.586 A:middle
notification queues to having

00:04:57.586 --> 00:04:59.856 A:middle
all visual, oral, and tactile

00:04:59.856 --> 00:05:01.636 A:middle
feedback, we're enabling

00:05:01.636 --> 00:05:03.136 A:middle
everyone to get their

00:05:03.136 --> 00:05:04.016 A:middle
notifications.

00:05:04.506 --> 00:05:07.526 A:middle
And you may have heard the

00:05:07.526 --> 00:05:09.786 A:middle
statistic that 1 in 68 children

00:05:09.786 --> 00:05:10.956 A:middle
in the United States have been

00:05:10.956 --> 00:05:13.036 A:middle
identified with the autism

00:05:13.036 --> 00:05:14.776 A:middle
spectrum disorder, according to

00:05:14.776 --> 00:05:15.366 A:middle
the CDC.

00:05:16.016 --> 00:05:17.746 A:middle
Autistic individuals can be

00:05:17.746 --> 00:05:20.156 A:middle
sensitive to unexpected sounds

00:05:20.156 --> 00:05:21.636 A:middle
and distracting graphics.

00:05:22.146 --> 00:05:24.016 A:middle
And there are also many adults

00:05:24.016 --> 00:05:25.396 A:middle
and children with dyslexia.

00:05:26.206 --> 00:05:28.076 A:middle
Having multiple visual and

00:05:28.076 --> 00:05:29.896 A:middle
auditory options help people

00:05:29.896 --> 00:05:32.716 A:middle
with dyslexia and is also widely

00:05:32.716 --> 00:05:34.186 A:middle
used by the blind and people

00:05:34.186 --> 00:05:34.976 A:middle
with low vision.

00:05:36.246 --> 00:05:37.776 A:middle
So, if we think about how

00:05:37.776 --> 00:05:39.126 A:middle
everyone in the world will have

00:05:39.126 --> 00:05:40.756 A:middle
a range of abilities and

00:05:40.756 --> 00:05:42.856 A:middle
capabilities, the next step of

00:05:42.856 --> 00:05:46.476 A:middle
reaching more people is making

00:05:46.476 --> 00:05:47.886 A:middle
your apps accessible.

00:05:48.496 --> 00:05:50.986 A:middle
But the word accessible wasn't

00:05:51.106 --> 00:05:52.326 A:middle
invented to describe

00:05:52.326 --> 00:05:53.346 A:middle
accommodating those with

00:05:53.346 --> 00:05:54.136 A:middle
disabilities.

00:05:54.566 --> 00:05:56.896 A:middle
It's about access, whoever we

00:05:56.896 --> 00:05:57.176 A:middle
are.

00:05:58.106 --> 00:05:59.806 A:middle
Easily reached or obtained.

00:05:59.926 --> 00:06:00.896 A:middle
Easily used.

00:06:01.036 --> 00:06:02.396 A:middle
Easily understood.

00:06:03.346 --> 00:06:05.396 A:middle
Everyone. Whether you have a

00:06:05.396 --> 00:06:06.706 A:middle
permanent or situational

00:06:06.706 --> 00:06:09.856 A:middle
impairment, young or old, new or

00:06:09.856 --> 00:06:11.316 A:middle
pro to technology.

00:06:11.736 --> 00:06:13.596 A:middle
Whatever language you sign,

00:06:13.596 --> 00:06:16.976 A:middle
speak, or read would love access

00:06:17.016 --> 00:06:19.566 A:middle
to great apps.

00:06:20.046 --> 00:06:22.066 A:middle
Together, we can design better

00:06:22.066 --> 00:06:23.256 A:middle
apps for everyone.

00:06:24.206 --> 00:06:25.396 A:middle
To help you do this, we're going

00:06:25.396 --> 00:06:26.646 A:middle
to talk about some design

00:06:26.646 --> 00:06:28.206 A:middle
considerations and workflow

00:06:28.206 --> 00:06:30.216 A:middle
techniques to keep in mind when

00:06:30.216 --> 00:06:31.426 A:middle
making your apps work for more

00:06:31.426 --> 00:06:31.826 A:middle
people.

00:06:32.626 --> 00:06:35.066 A:middle
By being inclusive, not only can

00:06:35.266 --> 00:06:36.816 A:middle
we help everyone function in

00:06:36.816 --> 00:06:37.686 A:middle
their daily life.

00:06:37.816 --> 00:06:38.936 A:middle
But we can also create new

00:06:38.936 --> 00:06:40.686 A:middle
possibilities throughout

00:06:40.686 --> 00:06:41.306 A:middle
society.

00:06:41.766 --> 00:06:43.666 A:middle
So, today, we're going to talk

00:06:43.666 --> 00:06:45.486 A:middle
about three areas of designing

00:06:45.486 --> 00:06:46.146 A:middle
for everyone.

00:06:47.156 --> 00:06:49.626 A:middle
Striving for simplicity, making

00:06:49.626 --> 00:06:51.326 A:middle
our apps effortless and easy to

00:06:51.326 --> 00:06:51.756 A:middle
learn.

00:06:53.436 --> 00:06:56.026 A:middle
Accessing perceivability.

00:06:56.206 --> 00:06:57.766 A:middle
Making sure our apps are

00:06:57.766 --> 00:06:59.336 A:middle
understandable through sight,

00:06:59.336 --> 00:07:00.636 A:middle
sound, and haptics.

00:07:01.256 --> 00:07:04.446 A:middle
And designing with integrity.

00:07:04.676 --> 00:07:06.276 A:middle
Holding ourselves accountable

00:07:06.276 --> 00:07:08.026 A:middle
for ethically making sure we

00:07:08.026 --> 00:07:09.116 A:middle
include everyone.

00:07:10.036 --> 00:07:11.796 A:middle
These are principles applied to

00:07:11.796 --> 00:07:13.276 A:middle
making great experiences,

00:07:13.586 --> 00:07:14.166 A:middle
period.

00:07:16.556 --> 00:07:19.266 A:middle
So, first if we think about

00:07:19.266 --> 00:07:20.586 A:middle
something that is simple to do,

00:07:20.996 --> 00:07:22.446 A:middle
we think of it being effortless

00:07:22.556 --> 00:07:24.456 A:middle
without difficulties, hurdles,

00:07:24.456 --> 00:07:25.746 A:middle
or cognitive strain.

00:07:26.626 --> 00:07:28.426 A:middle
But for something to feel simple

00:07:28.426 --> 00:07:29.646 A:middle
that does mean it can't do

00:07:29.646 --> 00:07:30.626 A:middle
complex things.

00:07:31.406 --> 00:07:32.776 A:middle
It just means trying to achieve

00:07:32.776 --> 00:07:34.546 A:middle
desired outcomes in the most

00:07:34.546 --> 00:07:35.956 A:middle
effortless and elegant way

00:07:35.956 --> 00:07:36.596 A:middle
possible.

00:07:37.586 --> 00:07:38.986 A:middle
Things that aren't simple create

00:07:38.986 --> 00:07:41.156 A:middle
barriers of entry to everyone.

00:07:41.756 --> 00:07:45.996 A:middle
As we go through our day, the

00:07:45.996 --> 00:07:47.476 A:middle
requirements of work and life

00:07:47.606 --> 00:07:49.086 A:middle
slowly drains our energy.

00:07:49.796 --> 00:07:51.656 A:middle
And when we are low on energy,

00:07:51.886 --> 00:07:53.356 A:middle
we have less energy to

00:07:53.356 --> 00:07:55.176 A:middle
troubleshoot tech and less

00:07:55.176 --> 00:07:56.306 A:middle
patience for navigating

00:07:56.306 --> 00:07:57.286 A:middle
something that should be quick

00:07:57.286 --> 00:07:57.796 A:middle
and easy.

00:07:59.066 --> 00:08:01.476 A:middle
At night, we rest and recharge.

00:08:03.456 --> 00:08:06.206 A:middle
However, were you aware that one

00:08:06.206 --> 00:08:07.556 A:middle
in six children in the United

00:08:07.556 --> 00:08:08.746 A:middle
States have a developmental

00:08:08.746 --> 00:08:09.636 A:middle
disability?

00:08:10.316 --> 00:08:11.346 A:middle
It ranges from mild

00:08:11.346 --> 00:08:12.636 A:middle
disabilities, such as speech and

00:08:12.636 --> 00:08:14.566 A:middle
language impairments to serious

00:08:14.566 --> 00:08:16.366 A:middle
developmental disabilities, such

00:08:16.366 --> 00:08:18.026 A:middle
as intellectual disabilities and

00:08:18.026 --> 00:08:18.616 A:middle
autism.

00:08:19.836 --> 00:08:21.696 A:middle
For people who have cognitive

00:08:21.696 --> 00:08:23.486 A:middle
disabilities and/or chronic

00:08:23.486 --> 00:08:25.546 A:middle
illnesses, they might start out

00:08:25.546 --> 00:08:27.206 A:middle
the day at three-quarters of a

00:08:27.206 --> 00:08:27.536 A:middle
tank.

00:08:28.006 --> 00:08:29.686 A:middle
And tasks take extra effort

00:08:29.686 --> 00:08:30.726 A:middle
throughout the day.

00:08:31.646 --> 00:08:34.016 A:middle
Plus, if you exert yourself all

00:08:34.016 --> 00:08:35.886 A:middle
the way to empty on one day, you

00:08:36.186 --> 00:08:37.496 A:middle
might start out the next day,

00:08:37.496 --> 00:08:38.486 A:middle
extremely low.

00:08:39.566 --> 00:08:42.026 A:middle
So, the apps that we make do a

00:08:42.026 --> 00:08:44.186 A:middle
great job at helping us through

00:08:44.186 --> 00:08:44.626 A:middle
our day.

00:08:45.076 --> 00:08:46.706 A:middle
Whether it's a convenience or

00:08:46.706 --> 00:08:48.046 A:middle
helping us to recharge.

00:08:49.676 --> 00:08:51.046 A:middle
They provide quick and easy

00:08:51.046 --> 00:08:53.196 A:middle
access to services, which is

00:08:53.196 --> 00:08:55.296 A:middle
extremely important for those

00:08:55.386 --> 00:08:56.346 A:middle
who may have difficulty

00:08:56.346 --> 00:08:57.766 A:middle
traveling outside of the home,

00:08:58.106 --> 00:08:59.596 A:middle
speaking a hearing on the phone,

00:09:00.076 --> 00:09:01.826 A:middle
or juggling work and home life.

00:09:03.566 --> 00:09:06.026 A:middle
For example, convenience apps

00:09:06.026 --> 00:09:08.346 A:middle
like Instacart, you can have

00:09:08.346 --> 00:09:10.086 A:middle
groceries delivered to your door

00:09:10.566 --> 00:09:11.756 A:middle
which alleviates the stress of

00:09:11.756 --> 00:09:13.836 A:middle
the supermarket, or allows you

00:09:13.836 --> 00:09:14.686 A:middle
to rest at home.

00:09:14.746 --> 00:09:16.816 A:middle
Or maybe it just gives you time

00:09:16.816 --> 00:09:17.806 A:middle
back with your family.

00:09:19.646 --> 00:09:20.886 A:middle
With education apps like

00:09:20.886 --> 00:09:23.366 A:middle
Doulingo it's incredible that we

00:09:23.366 --> 00:09:25.636 A:middle
can learn from the comforts of

00:09:25.636 --> 00:09:28.046 A:middle
our home, on our own time, at

00:09:28.046 --> 00:09:31.716 A:middle
our own speed, and with health

00:09:31.716 --> 00:09:33.756 A:middle
apps like Calm, they help us

00:09:33.756 --> 00:09:35.466 A:middle
nurture our mental and physical

00:09:35.466 --> 00:09:36.166 A:middle
well-being.

00:09:36.796 --> 00:09:39.716 A:middle
And with content creation apps

00:09:39.716 --> 00:09:41.696 A:middle
like iMovie, we can create and

00:09:41.696 --> 00:09:43.676 A:middle
share our artistry with friends,

00:09:43.716 --> 00:09:44.996 A:middle
family and the world.

00:09:46.636 --> 00:09:48.526 A:middle
So, apps play a key role in our

00:09:48.526 --> 00:09:49.626 A:middle
daily lives now.

00:09:50.086 --> 00:09:51.906 A:middle
And we can make even more impact

00:09:52.016 --> 00:09:53.756 A:middle
in people's lives by reducing

00:09:53.756 --> 00:09:55.376 A:middle
the amount of effort that we

00:09:55.376 --> 00:09:57.726 A:middle
require to use our apps, which

00:09:57.726 --> 00:10:00.116 A:middle
reduces barriers and provides

00:10:00.116 --> 00:10:01.016 A:middle
more access.

00:10:02.046 --> 00:10:03.196 A:middle
But this is easier said than

00:10:03.196 --> 00:10:03.556 A:middle
done.

00:10:03.796 --> 00:10:04.856 A:middle
So here are some ideas.

00:10:06.356 --> 00:10:08.416 A:middle
We should strive for our apps to

00:10:08.416 --> 00:10:10.406 A:middle
be easy to navigate by having

00:10:10.406 --> 00:10:11.816 A:middle
them similarly structured.

00:10:11.816 --> 00:10:14.826 A:middle
We need to be able to get

00:10:14.876 --> 00:10:17.106 A:middle
started and complete common task

00:10:17.256 --> 00:10:18.636 A:middle
without encountering any

00:10:18.636 --> 00:10:19.996 A:middle
barriers or issues.

00:10:21.636 --> 00:10:23.616 A:middle
And we should use UIKit as much

00:10:23.616 --> 00:10:25.236 A:middle
as possible to achieve the

00:10:25.236 --> 00:10:27.086 A:middle
consistent behaviors within each

00:10:27.086 --> 00:10:28.566 A:middle
app and across apps.

00:10:29.016 --> 00:10:30.966 A:middle
Because UIKit wasn't made for

00:10:30.966 --> 00:10:32.006 A:middle
just developers.

00:10:32.226 --> 00:10:33.856 A:middle
It's a design language for the

00:10:33.856 --> 00:10:35.886 A:middle
platform that everyone is

00:10:35.956 --> 00:10:37.466 A:middle
familiar with and knows how to

00:10:37.466 --> 00:10:37.966 A:middle
use.

00:10:38.506 --> 00:10:41.506 A:middle
And there are design resources

00:10:41.506 --> 00:10:43.386 A:middle
on human interface guidelines to

00:10:43.386 --> 00:10:45.026 A:middle
help you use the standard UIKit

00:10:45.026 --> 00:10:46.866 A:middle
components in your apps during

00:10:46.866 --> 00:10:47.596 A:middle
the design phase.

00:10:48.316 --> 00:10:50.356 A:middle
It's important to remember that

00:10:50.356 --> 00:10:52.256 A:middle
these toolkits support many

00:10:52.256 --> 00:10:54.146 A:middle
accessibility accommodations.

00:10:55.456 --> 00:10:58.086 A:middle
And if we can consistently use

00:10:58.086 --> 00:10:59.496 A:middle
standard UIKit interaction

00:10:59.496 --> 00:11:01.416 A:middle
patterns and components for more

00:11:01.416 --> 00:11:03.446 A:middle
task of our apps like basic

00:11:03.446 --> 00:11:05.096 A:middle
structure and navigation,

00:11:05.466 --> 00:11:07.566 A:middle
sign-up flows, account settings,

00:11:07.566 --> 00:11:10.846 A:middle
and sharing then you can spend

00:11:10.846 --> 00:11:12.596 A:middle
the majority of your time on the

00:11:12.596 --> 00:11:14.116 A:middle
parts of your apps that make

00:11:14.116 --> 00:11:14.746 A:middle
them special.

00:11:15.426 --> 00:11:17.076 A:middle
And making sure those parts are

00:11:17.076 --> 00:11:17.966 A:middle
accessible too.

00:11:19.596 --> 00:11:21.226 A:middle
Consistent use of our design

00:11:21.226 --> 00:11:23.166 A:middle
language is beneficial because

00:11:23.166 --> 00:11:25.066 A:middle
if you learn one app you have a

00:11:25.136 --> 00:11:27.386 A:middle
serious head start on learning

00:11:27.386 --> 00:11:30.996 A:middle
another because repetition

00:11:30.996 --> 00:11:32.676 A:middle
creates cognitive ease and a

00:11:32.676 --> 00:11:33.766 A:middle
comforting feeling of

00:11:33.766 --> 00:11:34.546 A:middle
familiarity.

00:11:35.086 --> 00:11:37.846 A:middle
But we know it's not always

00:11:37.846 --> 00:11:40.176 A:middle
possible, to solely use UIKit.

00:11:40.176 --> 00:11:41.326 A:middle
There are times when you need to

00:11:41.326 --> 00:11:42.546 A:middle
do something unique and

00:11:42.546 --> 00:11:44.626 A:middle
original, but don't forget about

00:11:44.626 --> 00:11:45.406 A:middle
accessibility.

00:11:45.406 --> 00:11:47.276 A:middle
It makes you think more

00:11:47.276 --> 00:11:48.636 A:middle
holistically about the products

00:11:48.636 --> 00:11:49.526 A:middle
that you're putting out into the

00:11:49.526 --> 00:11:49.856 A:middle
world.

00:11:51.336 --> 00:11:52.886 A:middle
So, simplicity.

00:11:52.886 --> 00:11:54.536 A:middle
Building on what I know.

00:11:54.916 --> 00:11:57.006 A:middle
Making use of standard

00:11:57.006 --> 00:11:58.486 A:middle
components and familiar

00:11:58.486 --> 00:12:00.266 A:middle
interaction patterns to help

00:12:00.266 --> 00:12:02.846 A:middle
make apps easy to navigate.

00:12:03.766 --> 00:12:05.436 A:middle
Be laser focused in your

00:12:05.436 --> 00:12:06.056 A:middle
objectives.

00:12:06.526 --> 00:12:07.726 A:middle
Reduce any hurdles.

00:12:08.066 --> 00:12:09.616 A:middle
Help me get started quickly.

00:12:09.616 --> 00:12:12.286 A:middle
And it just works like I

00:12:12.286 --> 00:12:13.936 A:middle
expected it to consistently.

00:12:16.596 --> 00:12:20.146 A:middle
So, our products need to be

00:12:20.146 --> 00:12:22.086 A:middle
understandable and perceivable

00:12:22.086 --> 00:12:22.696 A:middle
to everyone.

00:12:23.656 --> 00:12:25.186 A:middle
This means that information

00:12:25.586 --> 00:12:27.046 A:middle
needs to be available to at

00:12:27.046 --> 00:12:29.196 A:middle
least one sense; sight, sound or

00:12:29.196 --> 00:12:31.156 A:middle
touch that is available to each

00:12:31.156 --> 00:12:31.606 A:middle
person.

00:12:31.856 --> 00:12:34.606 A:middle
And we can look at our apps and

00:12:34.666 --> 00:12:36.736 A:middle
ask ourselves is it legible?

00:12:36.736 --> 00:12:38.526 A:middle
Is it audible?

00:12:38.526 --> 00:12:39.956 A:middle
And is it tactile?

00:12:41.366 --> 00:12:43.396 A:middle
But before we look at

00:12:43.396 --> 00:12:44.506 A:middle
legibility.

00:12:44.506 --> 00:12:45.976 A:middle
Let's escape for a moment to

00:12:45.976 --> 00:12:47.056 A:middle
this beautiful beach and

00:12:47.056 --> 00:12:49.586 A:middle
experience it in a few different

00:12:49.586 --> 00:12:49.866 A:middle
ways.

00:12:51.656 --> 00:12:54.396 A:middle
Relax, watch the waves roll in

00:12:54.396 --> 00:12:54.816 A:middle
and out.

00:12:55.186 --> 00:12:56.596 A:middle
Soak up that sunshine for a

00:12:56.596 --> 00:12:56.936 A:middle
second.

00:13:02.056 --> 00:13:03.326 A:middle
And if you have vision loss, you

00:13:03.326 --> 00:13:05.136 A:middle
might not get to see this in all

00:13:05.136 --> 00:13:07.096 A:middle
of its glory, but you're hearing

00:13:07.346 --> 00:13:08.786 A:middle
would be more sensitive to these

00:13:08.826 --> 00:13:09.686 A:middle
beautiful sounds.

00:13:10.516 --> 00:13:15.806 A:middle
[ Ocean Sounds ]

00:13:16.306 --> 00:13:18.056 A:middle
Or if you're colorblind, you

00:13:18.056 --> 00:13:19.346 A:middle
might see the world more like

00:13:19.426 --> 00:13:19.606 A:middle
this.

00:13:24.176 --> 00:13:26.066 A:middle
Or if you're blind, you're

00:13:26.066 --> 00:13:28.076 A:middle
likely even more in-tune to the

00:13:31.716 --> 00:13:31.836 A:middle
sound.

00:13:33.096 --> 00:13:34.656 A:middle
And these situations are very

00:13:34.656 --> 00:13:35.066 A:middle
real.

00:13:35.146 --> 00:13:38.316 A:middle
In the world, 285 million people

00:13:38.316 --> 00:13:39.616 A:middle
are estimated to have moderate

00:13:39.616 --> 00:13:41.576 A:middle
or severe vision loss.

00:13:41.986 --> 00:13:43.946 A:middle
And 39 million of those are

00:13:43.946 --> 00:13:44.736 A:middle
completely blind.

00:13:46.736 --> 00:13:48.566 A:middle
And one in 12 men are

00:13:48.566 --> 00:13:49.286 A:middle
colorblind.

00:13:50.856 --> 00:13:52.326 A:middle
And best estimates are around

00:13:52.326 --> 00:13:54.696 A:middle
360 million people in the world

00:13:54.696 --> 00:13:56.226 A:middle
have disabling hearing loss.

00:13:56.776 --> 00:13:59.456 A:middle
Not only can hearing and vision

00:13:59.456 --> 00:14:00.856 A:middle
loss limit people from

00:14:00.856 --> 00:14:02.416 A:middle
distinguishing information, but

00:14:02.756 --> 00:14:04.236 A:middle
they will also be seeing and

00:14:04.236 --> 00:14:05.646 A:middle
hearing your brand in different

00:14:05.646 --> 00:14:06.806 A:middle
ways than you expected.

00:14:07.296 --> 00:14:09.916 A:middle
For example, someone with low

00:14:09.916 --> 00:14:13.066 A:middle
vision may see their phones like

00:14:13.066 --> 00:14:13.486 A:middle
this.

00:14:14.506 --> 00:14:16.086 A:middle
And if you aren't low vision

00:14:16.086 --> 00:14:17.836 A:middle
yourself, you can simulate low

00:14:17.836 --> 00:14:19.856 A:middle
vision by using a small blur in

00:14:19.856 --> 00:14:20.856 A:middle
your design software.

00:14:22.756 --> 00:14:24.376 A:middle
Now, people with low vision will

00:14:24.376 --> 00:14:26.126 A:middle
often learn the location of

00:14:26.126 --> 00:14:27.866 A:middle
icons as long as they don't

00:14:27.866 --> 00:14:28.176 A:middle
move.

00:14:28.656 --> 00:14:30.966 A:middle
But content areas are different.

00:14:30.966 --> 00:14:32.496 A:middle
So, they need to maintain high

00:14:32.616 --> 00:14:34.856 A:middle
visual contrast to increase

00:14:34.856 --> 00:14:35.636 A:middle
legibility.

00:14:36.676 --> 00:14:38.606 A:middle
So, if you get started, you

00:14:38.606 --> 00:14:41.536 A:middle
should ask yourself is your app

00:14:41.536 --> 00:14:41.986 A:middle
legible?

00:14:43.186 --> 00:14:45.296 A:middle
Because maximizing legibility is

00:14:45.296 --> 00:14:47.016 A:middle
the highest benefit on being

00:14:47.016 --> 00:14:49.146 A:middle
able to comprehend information

00:14:49.436 --> 00:14:51.416 A:middle
because it's less work on us to

00:14:51.416 --> 00:14:51.986 A:middle
interpret.

00:14:53.266 --> 00:14:55.106 A:middle
For example, when we have key

00:14:55.106 --> 00:14:56.996 A:middle
information that is low in

00:14:57.046 --> 00:14:59.946 A:middle
contrasts because of small fonts

00:15:00.356 --> 00:15:02.506 A:middle
and low color contrast ratios,

00:15:03.236 --> 00:15:04.376 A:middle
or thin fonts.

00:15:05.956 --> 00:15:08.356 A:middle
It may be painful to read and

00:15:08.356 --> 00:15:10.206 A:middle
you experience cognitive strain.

00:15:10.806 --> 00:15:13.866 A:middle
So, a good place to start to

00:15:13.866 --> 00:15:15.856 A:middle
correct low contrast is to use

00:15:15.856 --> 00:15:18.966 A:middle
the default textile body for

00:15:18.966 --> 00:15:20.496 A:middle
your main content and a high

00:15:20.496 --> 00:15:22.346 A:middle
color contrast with your

00:15:22.346 --> 00:15:22.936 A:middle
background.

00:15:23.776 --> 00:15:25.716 A:middle
And then you can use bolder font

00:15:25.716 --> 00:15:28.976 A:middle
weights to emphasize text or

00:15:28.976 --> 00:15:30.826 A:middle
titles, rather than thin fonts.

00:15:31.756 --> 00:15:33.516 A:middle
And you can use filled in button

00:15:33.516 --> 00:15:36.076 A:middle
shapes so that the text contrast

00:15:36.076 --> 00:15:38.646 A:middle
is high, and the way forward in

00:15:38.646 --> 00:15:40.126 A:middle
your app is really clear.

00:15:40.776 --> 00:15:43.866 A:middle
And if you don't use textiles or

00:15:43.866 --> 00:15:45.606 A:middle
system fonts in your app, it

00:15:45.606 --> 00:15:47.316 A:middle
would be ideal to support the

00:15:47.316 --> 00:15:49.216 A:middle
accessibility bold text

00:15:49.216 --> 00:15:51.356 A:middle
settings, which requires you to

00:15:51.356 --> 00:15:53.156 A:middle
increase your font weights by

00:15:53.156 --> 00:15:54.686 A:middle
two weights thicker when the

00:15:54.686 --> 00:15:55.446 A:middle
setting is on.

00:15:56.006 --> 00:15:57.256 A:middle
Now, this is built-in with

00:15:57.366 --> 00:15:58.636 A:middle
system fonts and textiles.

00:16:00.086 --> 00:16:02.616 A:middle
The new App Store design does an

00:16:02.616 --> 00:16:04.146 A:middle
excellent job at maximizing

00:16:04.146 --> 00:16:05.496 A:middle
legibility through its bold

00:16:05.496 --> 00:16:07.296 A:middle
typography, prominent buy

00:16:07.296 --> 00:16:10.566 A:middle
buttons, large fonts, and high

00:16:10.966 --> 00:16:12.586 A:middle
color contrast colors.

00:16:13.086 --> 00:16:13.946 A:middle
Great job guys.

00:16:14.596 --> 00:16:19.406 A:middle
On macOS, there are increased

00:16:19.406 --> 00:16:21.786 A:middle
contrast settings as well, that

00:16:21.786 --> 00:16:24.586 A:middle
when on all active controls

00:16:24.866 --> 00:16:27.506 A:middle
become higher contrast by making

00:16:27.506 --> 00:16:29.896 A:middle
backgrounds opaque, button

00:16:29.896 --> 00:16:31.716 A:middle
outlines becomes thicker and

00:16:31.716 --> 00:16:35.696 A:middle
darker and system colors become

00:16:35.696 --> 00:16:37.576 A:middle
darker to create high color

00:16:37.576 --> 00:16:38.706 A:middle
contrast ratios.

00:16:39.206 --> 00:16:40.646 A:middle
So now that you know to look

00:16:40.646 --> 00:16:42.176 A:middle
for, let's look at the before

00:16:42.176 --> 00:16:42.996 A:middle
and after again.

00:16:44.106 --> 00:16:44.666 A:middle
Before.

00:16:45.996 --> 00:16:46.766 A:middle
After.

00:16:47.876 --> 00:16:50.206 A:middle
And even the ruled lines and the

00:16:50.206 --> 00:16:52.176 A:middle
color values of gray text

00:16:52.176 --> 00:16:53.016 A:middle
becomes darker.

00:16:54.106 --> 00:16:55.726 A:middle
You will need to supply these

00:16:55.766 --> 00:16:57.316 A:middle
same alternate designs, if you

00:16:57.316 --> 00:16:58.876 A:middle
do not use standard AppKit

00:16:59.066 --> 00:17:00.176 A:middle
because they will not come for

00:17:00.176 --> 00:17:02.126 A:middle
free in custom UI, but they're

00:17:02.126 --> 00:17:03.726 A:middle
extremely important for

00:17:03.726 --> 00:17:04.916 A:middle
maximizing legibility.

00:17:04.916 --> 00:17:08.576 A:middle
Now, the next suggestion to

00:17:08.576 --> 00:17:09.946 A:middle
increase legibility maybe the

00:17:09.946 --> 00:17:11.326 A:middle
most important thing to take

00:17:11.326 --> 00:17:11.906 A:middle
away today.

00:17:11.906 --> 00:17:14.376 A:middle
And that's to support dynamic

00:17:14.376 --> 00:17:16.136 A:middle
type, or the text size setting

00:17:17.096 --> 00:17:18.756 A:middle
because this feature increases

00:17:18.756 --> 00:17:20.296 A:middle
legibility by allowing each

00:17:20.296 --> 00:17:22.176 A:middle
person to personalize their

00:17:22.176 --> 00:17:23.486 A:middle
experience by increasing the

00:17:23.486 --> 00:17:24.176 A:middle
font size.

00:17:24.626 --> 00:17:26.646 A:middle
Or, maybe you need a farther

00:17:26.646 --> 00:17:28.966 A:middle
viewing distance if mounted on a

00:17:29.146 --> 00:17:30.616 A:middle
chair or propped on a table.

00:17:32.766 --> 00:17:34.016 A:middle
Because when our fonts don't

00:17:34.116 --> 00:17:35.976 A:middle
scale, people with low vision

00:17:35.976 --> 00:17:37.576 A:middle
need to use screen zoom windows

00:17:37.576 --> 00:17:38.866 A:middle
to read the content.

00:17:39.556 --> 00:17:41.286 A:middle
That's like having to turn your

00:17:41.286 --> 00:17:43.126 A:middle
light on, or your magnifier in a

00:17:43.126 --> 00:17:45.066 A:middle
dimly lit restaurant to read the

00:17:45.066 --> 00:17:45.566 A:middle
menu.

00:17:45.806 --> 00:17:47.946 A:middle
But except this is all day and

00:17:47.946 --> 00:17:48.456 A:middle
every day.

00:17:48.456 --> 00:17:51.366 A:middle
And some people don't bother

00:17:51.366 --> 00:17:52.516 A:middle
with zoom windows at all.

00:17:52.956 --> 00:17:54.296 A:middle
They painfully read the small

00:17:54.296 --> 00:17:56.086 A:middle
type or use their phones for

00:17:56.086 --> 00:17:57.276 A:middle
short periods of time.

00:17:57.536 --> 00:17:58.406 A:middle
And that's not a great

00:17:58.406 --> 00:17:59.036 A:middle
experience.

00:18:00.166 --> 00:18:02.356 A:middle
So, if you adopt dynamic type by

00:18:02.356 --> 00:18:04.486 A:middle
using textiles and use the new

00:18:04.526 --> 00:18:07.216 A:middle
standard spacing constraints, we

00:18:07.216 --> 00:18:08.596 A:middle
can offer a larger reading

00:18:08.596 --> 00:18:09.986 A:middle
experience without needing zoom

00:18:09.986 --> 00:18:10.416 A:middle
windows.

00:18:11.336 --> 00:18:13.476 A:middle
And new this year in iOS 11 is

00:18:13.476 --> 00:18:15.116 A:middle
dynamic type support for custom

00:18:15.116 --> 00:18:15.536 A:middle
fonts.

00:18:17.516 --> 00:18:19.276 A:middle
Additionally, if you access

00:18:19.366 --> 00:18:20.676 A:middle
larger text setting via the

00:18:20.676 --> 00:18:22.236 A:middle
general settings, there's a

00:18:22.236 --> 00:18:24.916 A:middle
switch that enables even larger

00:18:24.916 --> 00:18:26.586 A:middle
accessibility text sizes.

00:18:27.606 --> 00:18:29.586 A:middle
And this year, in iOS 11, all

00:18:29.586 --> 00:18:31.116 A:middle
textiles will support these

00:18:31.116 --> 00:18:31.906 A:middle
larger settings.

00:18:32.236 --> 00:18:34.306 A:middle
So, this means that we need to

00:18:34.306 --> 00:18:35.986 A:middle
design responsive layouts to be

00:18:35.986 --> 00:18:37.376 A:middle
able to handle these large font

00:18:37.376 --> 00:18:37.816 A:middle
sizes.

00:18:38.896 --> 00:18:40.806 A:middle
To do this for our own platform

00:18:40.966 --> 00:18:42.456 A:middle
apps this year, a team of us

00:18:42.456 --> 00:18:44.066 A:middle
took a step back and developed a

00:18:44.066 --> 00:18:45.916 A:middle
few simple principles that

00:18:45.916 --> 00:18:47.216 A:middle
helped guide us through a

00:18:47.216 --> 00:18:48.246 A:middle
system-wide audit.

00:18:49.556 --> 00:18:51.746 A:middle
The first principle was to make

00:18:51.746 --> 00:18:53.876 A:middle
as much text dynamic as possible

00:18:53.876 --> 00:18:54.836 A:middle
and to support these

00:18:54.836 --> 00:18:56.296 A:middle
accessibility text sizes.

00:18:57.646 --> 00:19:00.386 A:middle
Next is make good use of the

00:19:00.386 --> 00:19:02.436 A:middle
screen width by wrapping lines

00:19:02.436 --> 00:19:04.186 A:middle
of type, rather than truncating.

00:19:05.406 --> 00:19:07.316 A:middle
And then, displaying the same

00:19:07.316 --> 00:19:09.156 A:middle
amount of text at the larger

00:19:09.156 --> 00:19:11.066 A:middle
sizes as with the default UI.

00:19:12.456 --> 00:19:14.336 A:middle
And lastly, scaling glyphs that

00:19:14.336 --> 00:19:16.126 A:middle
appear next to text in content

00:19:16.126 --> 00:19:17.476 A:middle
areas so that the glyphs scale

00:19:17.476 --> 00:19:18.926 A:middle
with the text in harmony.

00:19:19.516 --> 00:19:21.486 A:middle
And when we look at all of these

00:19:21.486 --> 00:19:23.156 A:middle
together in practice it really

00:19:23.156 --> 00:19:23.916 A:middle
gets magical.

00:19:24.776 --> 00:19:27.106 A:middle
The mail screen now grows the

00:19:27.106 --> 00:19:29.206 A:middle
whole mail message to a zoom

00:19:29.206 --> 00:19:31.926 A:middle
level of 315% from the default

00:19:31.926 --> 00:19:32.366 A:middle
size.

00:19:33.456 --> 00:19:35.056 A:middle
And in custom layouts, like

00:19:35.056 --> 00:19:37.056 A:middle
calendar, this year we made even

00:19:37.056 --> 00:19:38.716 A:middle
more content scale like the

00:19:38.716 --> 00:19:40.596 A:middle
month grid increase in size,

00:19:41.106 --> 00:19:42.286 A:middle
where it didn't support dynamic

00:19:42.286 --> 00:19:43.216 A:middle
type it all before.

00:19:43.216 --> 00:19:45.826 A:middle
And at the larger accessibility

00:19:45.826 --> 00:19:48.126 A:middle
sizes, we re-laid out the event

00:19:48.286 --> 00:19:50.786 A:middle
row similar to the watch layout.

00:19:51.156 --> 00:19:52.466 A:middle
Because in the end, the

00:19:52.466 --> 00:19:54.056 A:middle
character count per line was

00:19:54.056 --> 00:19:54.916 A:middle
about the same.

00:19:54.986 --> 00:19:57.416 A:middle
And it allowed maximum screen

00:19:57.416 --> 00:19:58.356 A:middle
width for text.

00:19:59.046 --> 00:20:01.526 A:middle
So, now if we turn on the bold

00:20:01.526 --> 00:20:04.256 A:middle
text setting and simulate low

00:20:04.256 --> 00:20:05.836 A:middle
vision with the blur, and

00:20:06.866 --> 00:20:08.666 A:middle
compare it next to the largest

00:20:08.666 --> 00:20:10.236 A:middle
currently shipping screen on the

00:20:10.236 --> 00:20:12.496 A:middle
left, now people with vision

00:20:12.496 --> 00:20:14.016 A:middle
loss will be able to use this

00:20:14.016 --> 00:20:14.386 A:middle
app more.

