00:20:22.266 --> 00:20:23.526 A:middle
We've designed these responsive

00:20:23.526 --> 00:20:25.736 A:middle
layouts in most native UIKit

00:20:25.736 --> 00:20:26.426 A:middle
controls.

00:20:26.626 --> 00:20:28.356 A:middle
For example, like action sheets,

00:20:29.226 --> 00:20:31.286 A:middle
edit menus, and a keyboard auto

00:20:31.286 --> 00:20:32.046 A:middle
correction bar.

00:20:33.386 --> 00:20:34.736 A:middle
For elements like navigation

00:20:34.736 --> 00:20:36.386 A:middle
bars, toolbars, and tab bars

00:20:36.756 --> 00:20:37.796 A:middle
that would take up too much

00:20:37.796 --> 00:20:39.016 A:middle
space if we scaled them.

00:20:39.346 --> 00:20:41.086 A:middle
We added a larger representation

00:20:41.086 --> 00:20:42.776 A:middle
of the Fortis in a central hub

00:20:42.886 --> 00:20:44.616 A:middle
that you can get via Long Press.

00:20:45.936 --> 00:20:47.556 A:middle
And we also added larger

00:20:47.556 --> 00:20:49.796 A:middle
popovers for segmented controls.

00:20:50.446 --> 00:20:53.266 A:middle
And we've also extended larger

00:20:53.266 --> 00:20:55.026 A:middle
tech support to system spaces

00:20:55.026 --> 00:20:58.506 A:middle
like home screen app labels, and

00:20:58.506 --> 00:20:59.256 A:middle
notifications.

00:20:59.916 --> 00:21:01.696 A:middle
Now, there are a few we missed

00:21:01.696 --> 00:21:03.736 A:middle
this year, but we have plans for

00:21:03.736 --> 00:21:06.086 A:middle
more and if you support iKit,

00:21:06.086 --> 00:21:07.216 A:middle
you will get these updates for

00:21:07.216 --> 00:21:08.466 A:middle
free as we make them.

00:21:09.086 --> 00:21:12.236 A:middle
So, maximizing legibility and

00:21:12.236 --> 00:21:14.086 A:middle
providing scalable dynamic type

00:21:14.086 --> 00:21:16.246 A:middle
improves visual experience for

00:21:16.246 --> 00:21:16.756 A:middle
everyone.

00:21:18.076 --> 00:21:19.936 A:middle
And alongside text that is clear

00:21:19.936 --> 00:21:22.186 A:middle
and understandable, same applies

00:21:22.186 --> 00:21:23.576 A:middle
for media and games.

00:21:24.546 --> 00:21:26.516 A:middle
All dialogue should support

00:21:26.516 --> 00:21:28.636 A:middle
captions because captions

00:21:28.636 --> 00:21:30.286 A:middle
display what is being spoken,

00:21:30.496 --> 00:21:31.706 A:middle
which gives more access to

00:21:31.706 --> 00:21:33.126 A:middle
people, whether you have hearing

00:21:33.126 --> 00:21:35.006 A:middle
loss, in a public setting, or

00:21:35.006 --> 00:21:35.986 A:middle
maybe even learning a new

00:21:35.986 --> 00:21:36.516 A:middle
language.

00:21:37.466 --> 00:21:39.076 A:middle
It's like trying to watch a

00:21:39.076 --> 00:21:40.926 A:middle
video or a game intro with the

00:21:40.926 --> 00:21:42.456 A:middle
volume turned all the way down,

00:21:42.906 --> 00:21:45.576 A:middle
or trying to read someone's lips

00:21:45.576 --> 00:21:46.756 A:middle
that aren't looking at you.

00:21:46.956 --> 00:21:49.446 A:middle
It feels like you only get about

00:21:49.446 --> 00:21:50.326 A:middle
half the story.

00:21:51.806 --> 00:21:53.986 A:middle
So, apps like Kitchen Stories

00:21:53.986 --> 00:21:55.626 A:middle
have added captions to all of

00:21:55.626 --> 00:21:57.736 A:middle
their cooking videos, which is

00:21:58.436 --> 00:21:58.556 A:middle
great.

00:21:59.076 --> 00:22:01.616 A:middle
OK so along with sight is sound.

00:22:03.246 --> 00:22:04.626 A:middle
You can ask yourself, are your

00:22:04.626 --> 00:22:05.636 A:middle
apps audible?

