It knows the direction you're

00:28:48.346 --> 00:28:48.626 A:middle
facing.

00:28:50.006 --> 00:28:50.916 A:middle
It knows the device you're

00:28:50.916 --> 00:28:53.076 A:middle
using, and it's equipped with

00:28:53.076 --> 00:28:54.226 A:middle
your individual preferences.

00:28:55.696 --> 00:28:57.676 A:middle
It's updated every day with new

00:28:57.676 --> 00:28:58.236 A:middle
information.

00:28:58.726 --> 00:28:59.626 A:middle
And you can search it.

00:29:00.836 --> 00:29:02.606 A:middle
You can mark it indestructibly

00:29:02.926 --> 00:29:03.716 A:middle
and make it your own.

00:29:04.496 --> 00:29:07.166 A:middle
It can take you places in real

00:29:07.166 --> 00:29:08.866 A:middle
time, avoiding traffic,

00:29:09.706 --> 00:29:10.236 A:middle
hopefully.

00:29:11.286 --> 00:29:13.446 A:middle
And in iOS 11, you can even see

00:29:13.446 --> 00:29:14.286 A:middle
inside venues.

00:29:14.936 --> 00:29:18.966 A:middle
The point is, today our mediums

00:29:19.116 --> 00:29:21.316 A:middle
are so versatile, they provide

00:29:21.316 --> 00:29:22.246 A:middle
us with the incredible

00:29:22.246 --> 00:29:22.866 A:middle
opportunity.

00:29:25.896 --> 00:29:28.336 A:middle
So, when I joined Maps, I

00:29:28.336 --> 00:29:29.606 A:middle
remember thinking a lot about

00:29:29.606 --> 00:29:32.236 A:middle
how crazy it felt to see inside.

00:29:32.996 --> 00:29:34.386 A:middle
Like looking through a keyhole

00:29:34.956 --> 00:29:37.866 A:middle
and stepping through this icon,

00:29:37.866 --> 00:29:39.526 A:middle
I cannot have imagined the

00:29:39.526 --> 00:29:40.806 A:middle
operation I saw behind it.

00:29:41.546 --> 00:29:43.116 A:middle
I took it almost completely for

00:29:43.116 --> 00:29:43.556 A:middle
granted.

00:29:45.056 --> 00:29:46.646 A:middle
And everyone who uses our apps

00:29:46.646 --> 00:29:47.306 A:middle
are the same way.

00:29:48.456 --> 00:29:49.726 A:middle
They don't care how hard it was

00:29:49.786 --> 00:29:50.176 A:middle
to build.

00:29:51.406 --> 00:29:52.746 A:middle
It's not important that it works

00:29:52.786 --> 00:29:54.846 A:middle
for Johnny Appleseed or Jane

00:29:54.846 --> 00:29:55.086 A:middle
Doe.

00:29:56.466 --> 00:29:57.766 A:middle
What's important is that it

00:29:57.766 --> 00:29:58.576 A:middle
works for me.

00:29:59.886 --> 00:30:00.506 A:middle
Can I use it?

00:30:02.246 --> 00:30:03.796 A:middle
Imagine going to the movies.

00:30:04.796 --> 00:30:06.016 A:middle
You bought your ticket and your

00:30:06.016 --> 00:30:07.266 A:middle
excited to watch the film.

00:30:08.116 --> 00:30:08.736 A:middle
The theater's packed.

00:30:09.926 --> 00:30:11.526 A:middle
You get to your seat and there's

00:30:11.526 --> 00:30:12.676 A:middle
a pillar in front of it,

00:30:13.236 --> 00:30:14.396 A:middle
completely blocking your view.

00:30:15.676 --> 00:30:16.986 A:middle
I'm pretty sure I'm not going to

00:30:16.986 --> 00:30:17.946 A:middle
come back to that cinema.

00:30:18.526 --> 00:30:21.886 A:middle
And I'm no longer just a regular

00:30:21.886 --> 00:30:23.816 A:middle
Maps user, not that there's any

00:30:23.816 --> 00:30:24.326 A:middle
such thing.

00:30:25.616 --> 00:30:27.516 A:middle
We're trying to build a map of

00:30:27.516 --> 00:30:30.026 A:middle
the entire world and it's a big

00:30:30.026 --> 00:30:32.356 A:middle
and diverse place.

00:30:32.536 --> 00:30:34.286 A:middle
Like you, I'm on a team

00:30:34.286 --> 00:30:36.056 A:middle
responsible for everyone's

00:30:36.056 --> 00:30:36.546 A:middle
experience.

00:30:37.266 --> 00:30:40.766 A:middle
So, coming back to simplicity

00:30:40.866 --> 00:30:41.866 A:middle
and perceivability.

00:30:43.216 --> 00:30:45.396 A:middle
Maps are not exact replicas of

00:30:45.396 --> 00:30:46.026 A:middle
environments.

00:30:47.136 --> 00:30:49.176 A:middle
Sometimes photographic detail is

00:30:49.176 --> 00:30:49.636 A:middle
useful.

00:30:50.516 --> 00:30:52.396 A:middle
But most people don't find the

00:30:52.396 --> 00:30:53.976 A:middle
satellite view practical in

00:30:53.976 --> 00:30:55.306 A:middle
everyday life.

00:30:56.516 --> 00:30:59.056 A:middle
We use simplified abstracted

00:30:59.056 --> 00:31:01.366 A:middle
representations, designed to be

00:31:01.366 --> 00:31:03.186 A:middle
easy to understand and faster

00:31:03.186 --> 00:31:06.566 A:middle
for us to process to help us

00:31:06.566 --> 00:31:07.936 A:middle
orient ourselves more quickly.

00:31:08.526 --> 00:31:10.456 A:middle
And it's why we provide a

00:31:10.456 --> 00:31:11.356 A:middle
transit map too.

00:31:11.356 --> 00:31:13.946 A:middle
Where we suppress some elements,

00:31:14.456 --> 00:31:16.196 A:middle
like places or minor roads,

00:31:16.586 --> 00:31:17.846 A:middle
which aren't as relevant to you

00:31:18.096 --> 00:31:19.146 A:middle
once you're using transit.

00:31:20.156 --> 00:31:21.256 A:middle
And we do all this for

00:31:21.256 --> 00:31:21.876 A:middle
simplicity.

00:31:22.436 --> 00:31:26.176 A:middle
And we make sure our maps are

00:31:26.176 --> 00:31:26.896 A:middle
understandable.

00:31:27.796 --> 00:31:30.026 A:middle
Visually, audibly, and through

00:31:30.026 --> 00:31:30.886 A:middle
haptic feedback.

00:31:31.756 --> 00:31:33.556 A:middle
We put a lot of care into

00:31:33.556 --> 00:31:34.996 A:middle
keeping the navigation screen as

00:31:35.036 --> 00:31:35.956 A:middle
simple as possible.

00:31:36.496 --> 00:31:37.776 A:middle
The most important information

00:31:37.776 --> 00:31:39.346 A:middle
available at a glance.

00:31:39.396 --> 00:31:41.716 A:middle
So, you can understand quickly

00:31:42.116 --> 00:31:44.146 A:middle
and stay focused on the road.

00:31:44.706 --> 00:31:46.236 A:middle
And while you're walking or

00:31:46.236 --> 00:31:48.136 A:middle
taking transit, audible

00:31:48.136 --> 00:31:50.206 A:middle
directions spoken clearly.

00:31:51.076 --> 00:31:52.396 A:middle
&gt;&gt; Starting route to San Jose

00:31:52.396 --> 00:31:53.756 A:middle
McEnery Convention Center.

00:31:55.076 --> 00:31:56.976 A:middle
&gt;&gt; Imagine if Siri mumbled these

00:31:56.976 --> 00:31:59.106 A:middle
instructions incomprehensibly.

00:32:00.146 --> 00:32:01.526 A:middle
Because isn't that kind of the

00:32:01.526 --> 00:32:03.146 A:middle
equivalent to small, blurry

00:32:03.146 --> 00:32:03.706 A:middle
information.

00:32:04.296 --> 00:32:07.106 A:middle
And on your wrist, while your

00:32:07.106 --> 00:32:07.946 A:middle
phone is in your pocket,

00:32:08.416 --> 00:32:10.736 A:middle
different tactic sensations to

00:32:10.736 --> 00:32:13.366 A:middle
inform which way to turn and

00:32:14.216 --> 00:32:14.336 A:middle
when.

00:32:14.536 --> 00:32:16.336 A:middle
Altogether for perceivability.

00:32:17.156 --> 00:32:18.976 A:middle
It's legible, audible, and

00:32:19.216 --> 00:32:19.546 A:middle
tactile.

00:32:20.016 --> 00:32:23.316 A:middle
And you can use any one of these

00:32:24.586 --> 00:32:24.986 A:middle
distinctly.

00:32:24.986 --> 00:32:26.376 A:middle
Integrity is something different

00:32:26.376 --> 00:32:26.966 A:middle
conceptually.

00:32:27.796 --> 00:32:30.226 A:middle
We do things for simplicity and

00:32:30.226 --> 00:32:31.516 A:middle
to improve perceivability.

00:32:32.276 --> 00:32:34.036 A:middle
But we do things with integrity.

00:32:35.126 --> 00:32:36.676 A:middle
The state of being whole and

00:32:36.676 --> 00:32:37.196 A:middle
undivided.

00:32:39.216 --> 00:32:40.406 A:middle
When we say someone has

00:32:40.406 --> 00:32:42.056 A:middle
integrity with think of them as

00:32:42.056 --> 00:32:44.186 A:middle
being honest with an admirable

00:32:44.186 --> 00:32:45.026 A:middle
moral compass.

00:32:45.956 --> 00:32:47.066 A:middle
So, when we consider that the

00:32:47.066 --> 00:32:48.496 A:middle
people who need our services the

00:32:48.496 --> 00:32:50.546 A:middle
most, might be the ones who find

00:32:50.546 --> 00:32:52.846 A:middle
them the hardest to use, how do

00:32:52.846 --> 00:32:53.876 A:middle
we design with integrity.

00:32:55.446 --> 00:32:57.536 A:middle
Well, as designers and

00:32:57.536 --> 00:32:58.316 A:middle
developers, we take

00:32:58.316 --> 00:32:59.096 A:middle
responsibility.

00:33:00.446 --> 00:33:03.326 A:middle
When architects build spaces

00:33:03.326 --> 00:33:05.246 A:middle
today, they make sure they're

00:33:05.246 --> 00:33:07.356 A:middle
accessible for everyone because

00:33:07.356 --> 00:33:08.476 A:middle
it's a human right.

00:33:08.846 --> 00:33:10.586 A:middle
And when designer draw beautiful

00:33:10.586 --> 00:33:12.826 A:middle
cars, they still have to adhere

00:33:12.946 --> 00:33:15.506 A:middle
to regulations created for human

00:33:16.156 --> 00:33:16.316 A:middle
safety.

00:33:17.176 --> 00:33:18.566 A:middle
So, when we design digital

00:33:18.566 --> 00:33:20.716 A:middle
products, we have to hold

00:33:20.716 --> 00:33:21.966 A:middle
ourselves accountable for their

00:33:21.966 --> 00:33:23.146 A:middle
accessibility too.

00:33:23.666 --> 00:33:24.646 A:middle
Because when we don't we're

00:33:24.646 --> 00:33:25.676 A:middle
deciding who's important.

00:33:26.256 --> 00:33:30.326 A:middle
Last year for iOS 10, we

00:33:30.326 --> 00:33:31.926 A:middle
redesigned Maps from the ground

00:33:31.926 --> 00:33:32.436 A:middle
up.

00:33:33.616 --> 00:33:36.196 A:middle
Making it clearer, simpler, easy

00:33:36.196 --> 00:33:36.816 A:middle
to use, and faster.

00:33:37.216 --> 00:33:39.466 A:middle
And it was a big undertaking.

00:33:40.526 --> 00:33:41.456 A:middle
We opened the door on

00:33:41.536 --> 00:33:43.216 A:middle
accessibility, but we didn't go

00:33:43.216 --> 00:33:44.266 A:middle
that far along the corridor.

00:33:44.266 --> 00:33:45.866 A:middle
It was a busy year.

00:33:47.686 --> 00:33:49.226 A:middle
But in iOS 11 we did take

00:33:49.226 --> 00:33:51.276 A:middle
responsibility, and we made it a

00:33:51.326 --> 00:33:54.226 A:middle
priority, leveraging the new

00:33:54.226 --> 00:33:55.916 A:middle
UIKit frameworks and following

00:33:55.916 --> 00:33:57.326 A:middle
the principles that Caroline

00:33:57.326 --> 00:33:59.546 A:middle
outlined today.

00:33:59.736 --> 00:34:01.316 A:middle
Making as much text dynamic as

00:34:01.346 --> 00:34:03.776 A:middle
possible, displaying the same

00:34:03.776 --> 00:34:05.366 A:middle
amount of text as the default

00:34:05.366 --> 00:34:09.226 A:middle
UI, using as much of the screen

00:34:09.226 --> 00:34:11.696 A:middle
width for text.

00:34:11.696 --> 00:34:12.746 A:middle
Search is a core component of

00:34:12.746 --> 00:34:14.796 A:middle
Maps and now it's easier for

00:34:14.796 --> 00:34:15.476 A:middle
everyone to use.

00:34:16.106 --> 00:34:18.486 A:middle
But it's not always just as

00:34:18.516 --> 00:34:20.096 A:middle
simple as increasing the font

00:34:20.096 --> 00:34:20.316 A:middle
size.

00:34:21.106 --> 00:34:22.216 A:middle
And you might be thinking, hang

00:34:22.216 --> 00:34:24.166 A:middle
on, I can see some truncation in

00:34:24.166 --> 00:34:24.876 A:middle
these screenshots.

00:34:25.676 --> 00:34:26.846 A:middle
This breaks the principles we're

00:34:26.846 --> 00:34:28.466 A:middle
talking about, and you're right.

00:34:29.206 --> 00:34:30.456 A:middle
But sometimes we have to make

00:34:30.456 --> 00:34:32.126 A:middle
choices based on context.

00:34:33.196 --> 00:34:34.526 A:middle
Like, on the right screen here

00:34:34.526 --> 00:34:36.036 A:middle
the top of the card has a fixed

00:34:36.036 --> 00:34:36.316 A:middle
header.

00:34:37.036 --> 00:34:38.566 A:middle
So, if we didn't truncate, the

00:34:38.566 --> 00:34:40.296 A:middle
route options beneath would not

00:34:40.296 --> 00:34:40.906 A:middle
be scrollable.

00:34:41.666 --> 00:34:45.906 A:middle
Now, this is the card for a

00:34:45.906 --> 00:34:46.176 A:middle
place.

00:34:47.086 --> 00:34:47.806 A:middle
They're used in different

00:34:47.806 --> 00:34:50.516 A:middle
context across iOS, including

00:34:50.766 --> 00:34:53.046 A:middle
Spotlight, Safari, and Siri.

00:34:53.706 --> 00:34:55.376 A:middle
And from here you start

00:34:55.376 --> 00:34:58.106 A:middle
navigation, make a call to check

00:34:58.106 --> 00:34:58.996 A:middle
on your reservation.

00:34:59.926 --> 00:35:00.986 A:middle
Or even have a look at what's

00:35:00.986 --> 00:35:01.396 A:middle
inside.

00:35:02.156 --> 00:35:03.546 A:middle
Things everyone might like to

00:35:03.546 --> 00:35:03.660 A:middle
do.

00:35:05.136 --> 00:35:07.196 A:middle
So, let's take a closer look at

00:35:07.196 --> 00:35:08.306 A:middle
some of the components of this

00:35:08.386 --> 00:35:10.576 A:middle
design, like the title block.

00:35:10.576 --> 00:35:15.436 A:middle
We use this with search results

00:35:15.436 --> 00:35:18.106 A:middle
too and last year we truncated

00:35:18.106 --> 00:35:20.226 A:middle
the title for long place names

00:35:20.566 --> 00:35:21.436 A:middle
instead of wrapping.

00:35:22.556 --> 00:35:24.206 A:middle
But with a big of UIKit magic,

00:35:24.376 --> 00:35:28.336 A:middle
this year, now it does this.

00:35:28.546 --> 00:35:29.556 A:middle
Which is actually pretty cool.

00:35:29.556 --> 00:35:32.386 A:middle
And the component is more

00:35:32.386 --> 00:35:34.226 A:middle
effective and robust because of

00:35:34.856 --> 00:35:35.000 A:middle
it.

00:35:36.046 --> 00:35:37.126 A:middle
And we made some changes to the

00:35:37.126 --> 00:35:38.516 A:middle
place card this year to improve

00:35:38.516 --> 00:35:40.336 A:middle
hierarchy including this

00:35:40.336 --> 00:35:41.836 A:middle
secondary row of actions.

00:35:41.836 --> 00:35:44.336 A:middle
And we need to accommodate a

00:35:44.336 --> 00:35:45.996 A:middle
maximum of five options here.

00:35:47.006 --> 00:35:47.466 A:middle
Like these.

00:35:47.966 --> 00:35:50.196 A:middle
So, on an iPhone 7, in English,

00:35:51.646 --> 00:35:52.146 A:middle
hang on a sec.

00:35:53.736 --> 00:35:57.116 A:middle
That was such a cheap joke.

00:35:57.536 --> 00:36:00.686 A:middle
On iPhone 7, in English this

00:36:00.686 --> 00:36:02.336 A:middle
works and we can fit five in a

00:36:02.336 --> 00:36:02.403 A:middle
row.

00:36:02.403 --> 00:36:04.396 A:middle
But how do we handle it with

00:36:04.396 --> 00:36:05.056 A:middle
dynamic type?

00:36:05.266 --> 00:36:06.376 A:middle
Because we can't just increase

00:36:06.436 --> 00:36:07.106 A:middle
the font size.

00:36:07.246 --> 00:36:10.826 A:middle
But we could stack the UI

00:36:10.826 --> 00:36:12.006 A:middle
elements smartly.

00:36:12.006 --> 00:36:16.726 A:middle
And all the way up the scale.

00:36:17.416 --> 00:36:18.946 A:middle
Internationalization is a form

00:36:19.116 --> 00:36:20.186 A:middle
of accessibility too.

00:36:20.576 --> 00:36:21.366 A:middle
And it brings its own

00:36:21.366 --> 00:36:21.876 A:middle
challenges.

00:36:22.566 --> 00:36:23.986 A:middle
So, how about these labels in

00:36:23.986 --> 00:36:24.396 A:middle
Italian.

00:36:25.136 --> 00:36:27.716 A:middle
OK, they're a bit longer.

00:36:27.716 --> 00:36:31.036 A:middle
So, if we go back down to

00:36:31.876 --> 00:36:34.076 A:middle
default size, oh, but the label

00:36:34.076 --> 00:36:34.776 A:middle
is truncating.

00:36:34.866 --> 00:36:37.106 A:middle
And the label is important.

00:36:37.756 --> 00:36:39.446 A:middle
We should try not to truncate it

00:36:39.446 --> 00:36:40.026 A:middle
at any size.

00:36:40.026 --> 00:36:42.396 A:middle
But we could apply a similar

00:36:42.396 --> 00:36:45.256 A:middle
technique like this.

00:36:45.956 --> 00:36:48.126 A:middle
And now, they remain clear and

00:36:48.126 --> 00:36:48.796 A:middle
uncompromised.

00:36:50.276 --> 00:36:52.396 A:middle
Adaptive design based on a

00:36:52.396 --> 00:36:54.466 A:middle
user's language and UI settings.

00:36:55.186 --> 00:36:57.636 A:middle
And now it works better across

00:36:57.706 --> 00:36:58.956 A:middle
different device sizes too.

00:37:02.146 --> 00:37:03.256 A:middle
And for these actions at the

00:37:03.256 --> 00:37:05.166 A:middle
bottom of the card, as well as

00:37:05.166 --> 00:37:08.286 A:middle
all of the content, we reflowed

00:37:08.286 --> 00:37:13.276 A:middle
the labels and scaled the icons.

00:37:13.416 --> 00:37:15.206 A:middle
Using vector assets, so there's

00:37:15.206 --> 00:37:15.976 A:middle
no pixilation.

00:37:15.976 --> 00:37:18.326 A:middle
And of course, we made all the

00:37:18.326 --> 00:37:19.576 A:middle
labels VoiceOver enabled.

00:37:20.116 --> 00:37:21.586 A:middle
And in Maps, we hung out with

00:37:21.586 --> 00:37:22.186 A:middle
Siri as well.

00:37:22.806 --> 00:37:26.086 A:middle
So, there are more complex

00:37:26.086 --> 00:37:27.226 A:middle
challenges than the ones I just

00:37:27.226 --> 00:37:27.806 A:middle
illustrated.

00:37:28.626 --> 00:37:30.176 A:middle
And it's easier not to take

00:37:30.176 --> 00:37:30.926 A:middle
responsibility.

00:37:32.386 --> 00:37:33.766 A:middle
But challenges are rewarding.

00:37:34.776 --> 00:37:37.726 A:middle
And that's how I ended up;

00:37:38.006 --> 00:37:39.916 A:middle
challenges are fun and

00:37:39.916 --> 00:37:40.556 A:middle
rewarding.

00:37:40.556 --> 00:37:41.456 A:middle
And that's why I ended up

00:37:41.456 --> 00:37:42.996 A:middle
standing here today.

00:37:43.326 --> 00:37:44.426 A:middle
Designing for everyone is a

00:37:44.426 --> 00:37:46.336 A:middle
process that can bring a deeper

00:37:46.336 --> 00:37:49.056 A:middle
understanding of your product

00:37:49.706 --> 00:37:52.986 A:middle
and its purpose.

00:37:53.146 --> 00:37:54.796 A:middle
One of the few effective keys to

00:37:54.796 --> 00:37:55.716 A:middle
the design problem.

00:37:56.886 --> 00:37:58.616 A:middle
The ability of the designer to

00:37:58.616 --> 00:37:59.886 A:middle
recognize as many of the

00:37:59.886 --> 00:38:02.416 A:middle
constraints possible, their

00:38:02.416 --> 00:38:04.096 A:middle
willingness and enthusiasm for

00:38:04.336 --> 00:38:05.156 A:middle
working within these

00:38:05.156 --> 00:38:05.736 A:middle
constraints.

00:38:06.186 --> 00:38:09.496 A:middle
Because out of constraints come

00:38:09.496 --> 00:38:10.336 A:middle
great solutions.

00:38:10.856 --> 00:38:11.976 A:middle
And if we're designing just for

00:38:11.976 --> 00:38:14.156 A:middle
default settings, we're not

00:38:14.156 --> 00:38:14.906 A:middle
doing it right.

00:38:16.186 --> 00:38:17.266 A:middle
By trying to do better than

00:38:17.266 --> 00:38:19.226 A:middle
that, we make ourselves better.

00:38:20.036 --> 00:38:21.696 A:middle
And we really learned an awful

00:38:21.696 --> 00:38:22.000 A:middle
lot this year.

00:38:24.076 --> 00:38:26.686 A:middle
So, secondly after we decide to

00:38:26.686 --> 00:38:29.426 A:middle
take responsibility, we need to

00:38:29.426 --> 00:38:30.356 A:middle
think about empathy.

00:38:31.356 --> 00:38:32.796 A:middle
The ability to understand

00:38:32.796 --> 00:38:33.066 A:middle
people.

00:38:34.116 --> 00:38:35.746 A:middle
To recognize their wants,

00:38:36.116 --> 00:38:37.566 A:middle
desires, and feelings.

00:38:38.776 --> 00:38:40.456 A:middle
People that are not you --

00:38:41.286 --> 00:38:43.266 A:middle
because nobody else is.

00:38:43.336 --> 00:38:45.956 A:middle
So, let's take a look at a few

00:38:45.956 --> 00:38:48.396 A:middle
made-up examples that might be

00:38:48.396 --> 00:38:51.396 A:middle
closer to home.

00:38:51.616 --> 00:38:52.196 A:middle
Newspapers.

00:38:53.256 --> 00:38:54.616 A:middle
Never been accessible.

00:38:56.506 --> 00:38:57.306 A:middle
There's something nice to

00:38:57.306 --> 00:38:58.456 A:middle
sitting down with a newspaper,

00:38:58.456 --> 00:39:01.606 A:middle
but not if you can't read it.

00:39:02.736 --> 00:39:04.686 A:middle
If your vision isn't perfect,

00:39:04.686 --> 00:39:06.296 A:middle
reading one of these has always

00:39:06.296 --> 00:39:06.916 A:middle
been a challenge.

00:39:08.076 --> 00:39:09.116 A:middle
And a lot of you create

00:39:09.116 --> 00:39:10.386 A:middle
platforms for content that's

00:39:10.386 --> 00:39:12.746 A:middle
consumed the world over.

00:39:13.796 --> 00:39:15.816 A:middle
Platforms with the capabilities

00:39:16.886 --> 00:39:18.296 A:middle
to improve the readability of

00:39:18.296 --> 00:39:20.626 A:middle
our content, relatively and

00:39:20.626 --> 00:39:21.256 A:middle
automatically.

00:39:22.696 --> 00:39:24.016 A:middle
And platforms, which can be

00:39:24.016 --> 00:39:25.946 A:middle
navigated and understood through

00:39:25.946 --> 00:39:27.836 A:middle
sound for those who can't read

00:39:27.836 --> 00:39:28.236 A:middle
visually.

00:39:28.856 --> 00:39:32.576 A:middle
And we read a lot on our iPhones

00:39:32.766 --> 00:39:33.276 A:middle
or iPads.

00:39:33.996 --> 00:39:36.026 A:middle
Sometimes it's good news, other

00:39:36.026 --> 00:39:36.976 A:middle
times it's bad news.

00:39:37.666 --> 00:39:39.126 A:middle
Or, depending on where you look,

00:39:39.266 --> 00:39:42.946 A:middle
it could be fake news, like

00:39:42.946 --> 00:39:44.276 A:middle
these revelations about Lorem

00:39:44.276 --> 00:39:44.736 A:middle
ipsum.

00:39:47.926 --> 00:39:50.286 A:middle
So, here's the same article with

00:39:50.286 --> 00:39:51.776 A:middle
some visual considerations for

00:39:51.776 --> 00:39:52.756 A:middle
dynamic type.

00:39:53.856 --> 00:39:55.546 A:middle
The headline is moved outside

00:39:55.546 --> 00:39:57.176 A:middle
the hero image for better

00:39:57.176 --> 00:39:58.956 A:middle
contrast and for practicality.

00:40:00.046 --> 00:40:01.736 A:middle
And the content is readable at

00:40:01.736 --> 00:40:02.706 A:middle
my preferred size.

00:40:03.486 --> 00:40:05.226 A:middle
And it still looks great.

00:40:05.916 --> 00:40:07.526 A:middle
But what if you couldn't read a

00:40:07.526 --> 00:40:08.026 A:middle
price tag?

00:40:08.026 --> 00:40:10.296 A:middle
What would the experience of

00:40:10.356 --> 00:40:11.216 A:middle
buying things be like?

00:40:11.326 --> 00:40:14.676 A:middle
You can't tap on a price tag to

00:40:14.676 --> 00:40:17.646 A:middle
hear an audio cue, but on an

00:40:17.646 --> 00:40:19.866 A:middle
iPhone, iPad, or Mac you can do

00:40:19.866 --> 00:40:22.556 A:middle
exactly that and more.

00:40:22.796 --> 00:40:24.486 A:middle
So, here we are shopping for

00:40:24.596 --> 00:40:27.076 A:middle
fresh, delicious, emoji-fied

00:40:27.176 --> 00:40:27.686 A:middle
fruit.

00:40:28.666 --> 00:40:30.736 A:middle
And there's a two-column layout

00:40:30.736 --> 00:40:31.626 A:middle
at default settings.

00:40:32.126 --> 00:40:33.476 A:middle
So, if we turn up dynamic types

00:40:33.476 --> 00:40:36.096 A:middle
a bit, we could reflow the

00:40:36.096 --> 00:40:37.536 A:middle
content into one linear list.

00:40:38.966 --> 00:40:40.376 A:middle
Similar to how you would on a

00:40:40.376 --> 00:40:41.976 A:middle
responsive website between

00:40:41.976 --> 00:40:43.576 A:middle
desktop and mobile breakpoints.

00:40:44.446 --> 00:40:45.856 A:middle
Giving enough space to elements

00:40:46.186 --> 00:40:47.876 A:middle
to make them simpler and easier

00:40:48.736 --> 00:40:49.906 A:middle
to pass.

00:40:50.116 --> 00:40:51.256 A:middle
And here's our product page for

00:40:51.256 --> 00:40:51.886 A:middle
this pineapple.

00:40:53.946 --> 00:40:54.926 A:middle
Adapting your layout

00:40:54.926 --> 00:40:56.736 A:middle
appropriately makes sure the

00:40:56.736 --> 00:40:57.986 A:middle
most important actions are

00:40:57.986 --> 00:40:58.926 A:middle
available immediately.

00:40:59.906 --> 00:41:00.976 A:middle
So, again if we bump up the

00:41:00.976 --> 00:41:04.146 A:middle
dynamic type that's working

00:41:04.146 --> 00:41:04.536 A:middle
pretty well.

00:41:05.376 --> 00:41:06.846 A:middle
But, let's turn it up to the

00:41:06.846 --> 00:41:07.406 A:middle
maximum.

00:41:08.106 --> 00:41:11.336 A:middle
Nice, but is there more we can

00:41:11.336 --> 00:41:11.676 A:middle
do here?

00:41:12.576 --> 00:41:14.996 A:middle
If we scroll the card, we can

00:41:14.996 --> 00:41:17.326 A:middle
see the most desired actions are

00:41:17.326 --> 00:41:18.196 A:middle
a little bit far way.

00:41:19.016 --> 00:41:20.916 A:middle
So, maybe we'd consider swapping

00:41:20.916 --> 00:41:21.936 A:middle
them in this context.

00:41:22.706 --> 00:41:25.206 A:middle
Yes. And that's definitely

00:41:25.886 --> 00:41:26.016 A:middle
better.

00:41:26.976 --> 00:41:28.166 A:middle
Well, what about music,

00:41:29.116 --> 00:41:31.476 A:middle
podcasts, stories, sound?

00:41:32.826 --> 00:41:34.256 A:middle
Audio content is great because

00:41:34.256 --> 00:41:35.596 A:middle
it plays over the air, or your

00:41:35.596 --> 00:41:36.046 A:middle
headphones.

00:41:36.686 --> 00:41:37.776 A:middle
You don't need a UI to be

00:41:37.776 --> 00:41:38.636 A:middle
entertained by it.

00:41:39.396 --> 00:41:40.736 A:middle
But you do need a UI to be able

00:41:40.736 --> 00:41:42.186 A:middle
to discover it.

00:41:43.376 --> 00:41:45.076 A:middle
And in the new podcast and music

00:41:45.076 --> 00:41:47.086 A:middle
apps on iOS 11, the content

00:41:47.086 --> 00:41:48.686 A:middle
adapts to your preferences and

00:41:48.686 --> 00:41:50.246 A:middle
can be used with VoiceOver, so

00:41:50.246 --> 00:41:51.766 A:middle
everyone can access it.

00:41:52.396 --> 00:41:56.096 A:middle
Now, finally potential energy.

00:41:56.546 --> 00:41:57.586 A:middle
Unlocking potential.

00:41:58.236 --> 00:42:00.856 A:middle
If we make more things possible

00:42:01.316 --> 00:42:03.306 A:middle
for more types of people, more

00:42:03.306 --> 00:42:03.936 A:middle
things can happen.

00:42:05.146 --> 00:42:07.116 A:middle
Awesome things like iconic

00:42:07.176 --> 00:42:09.016 A:middle
albums or pioneering science.

00:42:10.006 --> 00:42:11.376 A:middle
Or miraculous things like

00:42:11.566 --> 00:42:13.646 A:middle
remembering your friends'

00:42:14.736 --> 00:42:14.946 A:middle
birthdays.

00:42:15.086 --> 00:42:16.526 A:middle
Simple things like sending a

00:42:16.526 --> 00:42:18.246 A:middle
gift or a message to a loved

00:42:18.866 --> 00:42:18.976 A:middle
one.

00:42:20.716 --> 00:42:21.886 A:middle
Can anyone read that?

00:42:24.386 --> 00:42:26.616 A:middle
We're reliant on language and

00:42:26.616 --> 00:42:29.306 A:middle
our remarkable use of it is

00:42:29.306 --> 00:42:30.696 A:middle
perhaps the primary reason for

00:42:30.696 --> 00:42:32.056 A:middle
our success as a species.

00:42:32.946 --> 00:42:34.576 A:middle
Be it through colors, text,

00:42:35.196 --> 00:42:36.566 A:middle
sound, or signs.

00:42:37.296 --> 00:42:40.276 A:middle
And what about now?

00:42:41.286 --> 00:42:42.586 A:middle
German speakers in the room are

00:42:42.586 --> 00:42:43.796 A:middle
one step ahead of us.

00:42:44.836 --> 00:42:45.886 A:middle
If we don't communicate in

00:42:45.886 --> 00:42:48.176 A:middle
everyone's language, how can we

00:42:48.176 --> 00:42:49.986 A:middle
help them accomplish things?

00:42:51.096 --> 00:42:53.336 A:middle
Without understanding, we can't

00:42:53.336 --> 00:42:54.436 A:middle
create any value at all.

00:42:54.506 --> 00:42:58.686 A:middle
I read an amazing article

00:42:58.686 --> 00:43:00.776 A:middle
earlier this week called, "The

00:43:00.836 --> 00:43:02.896 A:middle
Thoughts of a Spider Web" by

00:43:02.896 --> 00:43:03.756 A:middle
Joshua Sokol.

00:43:04.936 --> 00:43:06.366 A:middle
And in it there was an example

00:43:07.056 --> 00:43:09.486 A:middle
about how bees use ultraviolet

00:43:09.486 --> 00:43:11.806 A:middle
vision to find flowers that have

00:43:11.806 --> 00:43:13.406 A:middle
also evolved ultraviolet

00:43:13.406 --> 00:43:13.836 A:middle
markings.

00:43:15.186 --> 00:43:16.426 A:middle
And beside it a quote which

00:43:16.456 --> 00:43:19.106 A:middle
said, "if you don't have those

00:43:19.106 --> 00:43:21.736 A:middle
receptors that part of the world

00:43:21.736 --> 00:43:23.526 A:middle
simply doesn't exist."

00:43:25.436 --> 00:43:27.626 A:middle
Design that includes everyone is

00:43:27.626 --> 00:43:30.206 A:middle
not good design, it's great

00:43:30.946 --> 00:43:31.096 A:middle
design.

00:43:32.116 --> 00:43:33.616 A:middle
So, design with integrity.

00:43:34.216 --> 00:43:36.056 A:middle
Take responsibility, caring

00:43:36.056 --> 00:43:38.156 A:middle
about everyone's experience, not

00:43:38.156 --> 00:43:38.696 A:middle
just your own.

00:43:39.886 --> 00:43:41.826 A:middle
And be empathetic considering

00:43:41.826 --> 00:43:43.676 A:middle
the perspectives of others who

00:43:43.676 --> 00:43:44.906 A:middle
interact with the world in

00:43:44.906 --> 00:43:46.676 A:middle
different ways than you do.

00:43:47.306 --> 00:43:49.436 A:middle
And understand that by doing so

00:43:49.436 --> 00:43:51.856 A:middle
we can help unlock potential, in

00:43:51.856 --> 00:43:53.276 A:middle
tiny and huge ways.

00:43:56.516 --> 00:44:01.846 A:middle
[ Applause ]

00:44:02.346 --> 00:44:04.556 A:middle
&gt;&gt; So, together we can strive

00:44:04.776 --> 00:44:06.486 A:middle
for simplicity and

00:44:06.486 --> 00:44:08.116 A:middle
perceivability in our apps.

00:44:08.296 --> 00:44:10.126 A:middle
And do it all with integrity for

00:44:10.126 --> 00:44:11.676 A:middle
making good apps great.

00:44:13.076 --> 00:44:14.896 A:middle
I encourage you to start now.

00:44:15.136 --> 00:44:17.026 A:middle
Go home and audit your apps.

00:44:17.216 --> 00:44:18.676 A:middle
Start conversations with your

00:44:18.676 --> 00:44:20.446 A:middle
team and people who use your

00:44:20.446 --> 00:44:20.906 A:middle
apps.

00:44:21.546 --> 00:44:22.986 A:middle
And most importantly schedule

00:44:22.986 --> 00:44:24.676 A:middle
time to see it all the way into

00:44:24.676 --> 00:44:25.596 A:middle
customers' hands.

00:44:26.666 --> 00:44:28.676 A:middle
And lastly do it proudly.

00:44:29.076 --> 00:44:31.346 A:middle
We can give everyone the chance

00:44:31.346 --> 00:44:33.406 A:middle
to be surprised, delighted, feel

00:44:33.406 --> 00:44:34.466 A:middle
good, and empowered.

00:44:35.366 --> 00:44:37.396 A:middle
We especially as designers would

00:44:37.396 --> 00:44:39.176 A:middle
always like things to line up

00:44:39.176 --> 00:44:40.916 A:middle
just right, but you can't

00:44:40.916 --> 00:44:42.206 A:middle
control every line break.

00:44:42.836 --> 00:44:44.566 A:middle
You can't control how someone

00:44:44.566 --> 00:44:45.796 A:middle
will need to personalize their

00:44:45.796 --> 00:44:47.706 A:middle
experience because everyone is

00:44:47.706 --> 00:44:48.136 A:middle
different.

00:44:48.136 --> 00:44:50.186 A:middle
And let's celebrate that.

00:44:52.516 --> 00:44:53.716 A:middle
&gt;&gt; We're really proud of what

00:44:53.716 --> 00:44:54.736 A:middle
we've achieved in Maps this

00:44:54.736 --> 00:44:57.056 A:middle
year, but there's more to do and

00:44:57.056 --> 00:44:57.806 A:middle
we're going to keep going,

00:44:58.026 --> 00:44:59.886 A:middle
because a map is never finished.

00:45:00.996 --> 00:45:02.086 A:middle
And everyone wants to find their

00:45:02.086 --> 00:45:02.296 A:middle
way.

00:45:02.696 --> 00:45:03.916 A:middle
So, we're designing for everyone

00:45:04.006 --> 00:45:05.046 A:middle
and we really hope you'll join

00:45:05.046 --> 00:45:06.386 A:middle
us on this mission.

00:45:07.516 --> 00:45:13.636 A:middle
[ Applause ]

